st: additional directions
tb: The Confession and Apostles' Creed may be omitted, provided each is said at least once during the course of the day.
tb: The Gloria Patri (Glory be...) in the opening versicles may be said in unison.
    The following form of the Gloria Patri may alternatively be used:
l:b:Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit:
l:b:i: As it was in the beginning, is now, and will be for ever. Amen.
tb: The Officiant and People may join in saying "Alleluia" (except in Lent) as an
    alternative to the versicles "Praise the Lord. The Lord's Name be praised."
tb: If an offering is to be received, it is appropriate to do so during the hymn or anthem following the Collects.
tb: A sermon may be preached after the lessons, after the hymn or anthem
    following the Collects, or after the conclusion of the Office.
